.TH CORTEX-SKILLS 1 "2026-03-23" "cortex-skills 2.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
cortex-skills \- Command-line tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cortex-skills
[
B-h
    R | 
        B--help
               R]
.br
.B cortex-skills

ICOMMAND
        R [
           ISUBCOMMAND
                      R] [
                          IARGS
                               R...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cortex-skills
.SH COMMANDS
Available commands:
.TP
.B list
List available skills
.TP
.B info
Show skill details
.TP
.B validate
Validate skill metadata
.TP
.B analyze
Analyze text and suggest matching skills
.TP
.B suggest
Suggest skills based on project context
.TP
.B metrics
Show skill usage metrics
.TP
.B deps
Show which agents use a skill
.TP
.B agents
Show which agents use a skill (alias for deps)
.TP
.B compose
Show dependency tree for a skill
.TP
.B versions
Show version information for a skill
.TP
.B analytics
Show skill effectiveness analytics
.TP
.B report
Generate comprehensive analytics report
.TP
.B trending
Show trending skills over time
.TP
.B recommend
Get AI-powered skill recommendations
.TP
.B feedback
Provide feedback on skill recommendations
.TP
.B context
Generate skill context for current session
.TP
.B rate
Rate a skill with stars and optional review
.TP
.B ratings
Show ratings and reviews for a skill
.TP
.B top-rated
Show top-rated skills
.TP
.B export-ratings
Export skill ratings data
.TP
.B community
Community skill commands
.TP
.B audit
Audit skill quality and completeness
.TP
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help message and exit
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT
Override for context directory (set automatically by Claude Code when running plugin commands)
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.claude/
Default context directory containing agents, modes, rules, and other configuration
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR cortex-skills-tui (1),
.BR cortex-skills-workflow (1)
